                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.796/150: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-28T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 28, 1941—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. Your 91, March 26, 3 p.m.<note n="15" xml:id="d404fn15">Not printed.</note>
                    Please express to the President of Peru<note n="16" xml:id="d404fn16">Manuel
                        Prado y Ugarteche.</note> on behalf of this Government hearty concurrence in
                    the position which the President of Peru has taken to the effect that aviation
                    services in this hemisphere should not be operated by non-American interests. It
                    is indeed gratifying to find this position so definitely implemented by the
                    cancellation by Peru of the Lufthansa<note n="17" xml:id="d404fn17">German
                        aviation company; its contract in Peru was cancelled on March 24.</note>
                    contract. This action makes a real contribution to continental solidarity and to
                    continental defense.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
